  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to investigate the incidence and predictive factors related to
      intestinal injury in patients undergoing heart valve replacement through a multicenter study
      in China.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Intestinal injury is one of main reasons for mobidity and mortality after heart valve
      replacement, but its incidence and potential risk factors remain unclear. A multicenter study
      in China is undertaken to investigate the incidence and predictive factors related to
      intestinal injury in patients undergoing heart valve replacement.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
